						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Chikarāja</hi> assigned, to the temple of Tripurāntakēśvara (?), the duties payable on salt imported into and sold in Tripurāntakam, the town of Tripurāntakēśvara. The grant is said to have been made for the merit of <hi rend="bold">Nūvula Rāmadēva Peggaḍa</hi> during the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kākatīya Gaṇapatidēva-Mahārāja.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
